\frame{
\frametitle{Derivation of reference points}
\bi The proposed form for managment rule is $C_y = H B_{75cm^+}$
\item No evidence of impaired recruitment and fishing mortality is considered to have been low
\item $B_{loss} = 9.93 kt$ is suggested as a candidate for $B_{pa}$
\item $B_{lim} = B_{pa}/1.4 = 7.09$
\item $H_{lim}$ set as the harvest rate that has 50\% chance of SSB being at $B_{lim}$ via stochastic simulation without assessment error
\item Variability in recruitment is based on a block bootstrap of estimated recruitment, block size of 6 consequtive years.
\item $F_{lim}$, $F_{pa}$ and $H_{pa}$ are estimated based on the estimate of $H_{lim}$
\item $H_{msy}$ is based on simulation with assessment error (lognormal with $\rho = 0.8$, and $\sigma$ as the CV of $B_{75cm^+}$)
\ei
}

